LAGOS  – The Lagos State Government has charged staff of the Lagos State Building Control Agency (LASBCA) on the consistent use of the Green Sticker for building control in the State. Dr. Idris Salako, the Commissioner for Physical Planning and Urban Development, gave this charge at a periodic meeting with management staff of LASBCA and Physical Planning Permit Authority (LASPPPA) He noted that the Green Sticker was conceived as a evidence of pass-mark on buildings monitored by the building control agency. He said: “ the presence of the Green Sticker on a building is an indication that the building, having been monitored by staff of LASBCA, has gone through compliance checks and complied to specific requirements”. Salako urged staff of the Agency to guide their integrity and be painstaking in the use of the Sticker, adding that professionalism should always be their watchwords. In the same vein, the Commissioner, who was corroborated by the Special Adviser on Urban Development, Ganiyu Adele Ayuba, Special Adviser, E-GIS, Dr. Olajide Babatunde and the Permanent Secretary in the Ministry, Engr. Abiola Kosegbe, called for collaboration between LASPPPA and LASBCA as they enjoined officers of the sister agencies to view their working together as an essential element of success in achieving a sustainable State.